de.emotreco.facialexpressionmodel

Class FacialExpression

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.emotreco.facialexpressionmodel.FacialExpression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<FacialExpression>

    public class FacialExpression
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<FacialExpression>
    A class representing the discrete values of an facial expression. An expression (expressionKey) can be "Stirnfalten" while its intensity (value) could be "high". This association is made with a certain confidence(confidence).

    • Constructor Detail

      • FacialExpression

        FacialExpression(java.lang.String expressionKey,
                 java.lang.String value,
                 float confidence)
        See keys from Emotions.java. Value kann be *one* of low, medium or high. Paste in the value resulting from the winner takes all principle.
        Parameters:
        expressionKey - e.g. "Stirnfalten"
        value - one of low, medium or high
        confidence - the confidence of this expression within the frame

      • getMatchingBinaries

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getMatchingBinaries()
        Get a list representing the emotions which would match expressionKey and value. Independant from confidence. Order is [NEUTRAL, SADNESS, FEAR, JOY, DISGUST].
        Returns:
        for example [0, 0, 0, 1, 0]
